
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `arch` baraye chap kardane nam-e architecture machine estefade mishavad. Yani neshan midahad computer az che noe CPU estefade mikonad (masalan x86_64 ya arm64).

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `arch` --> 🖥️ Namayesh architecture system-e ameli.
    🔹 `arch -k` --> 🔤 Namayesh architecture kernel. (Dar system-haye mac)
    🔹 `arch -x <architecture> <dastoor>` --> 🚀 Ejraye dastoor ba architecture moshakhas.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ arch

    🔹 Namayesh architecture فعلی سیستم.

    $ arch -k

    🔹 (Dar mac) Namayesh architecture هسته (kernel).

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ arch
    x86_64

    🔹 In neshan midahad ke computer shoma az architecture x86_64 estefade mikonad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `arch` command prints the machine architecture type. It shows what kind of CPU your computer is using (e.g., x86_64 or arm64).

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `arch` --> 🖥️ Display the operating system's architecture.
    🔹 `arch -k` --> 🔤 Display the kernel architecture (macOS only).
    🔹 `arch -x <architecture> <command>` --> 🚀 Run the specified command under the given architecture.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ arch

    🔹 Display the current system architecture.

    $ arch -k

    🔹 (On macOS) Display the kernel architecture.

✅ **Simple Example & Explanation:**

    $ arch
    x86_64

    🔹 This indicates that your computer uses the x86_64 architecture.
